The two biggest issues I flagged:

1. **Missing the SNL dimension entirely** — Goodman has hosted *Saturday Night Live* 13 times, third-most ever (behind only Baldwin and Steve Martin). It's both one of his most defining public roles and the cleanest possible proof of the draft's thesis: a Type 9 who keeps returning to a "family" that isn't even his own show. Right now "attaches to families and stays" rests entirely on the Coens and *Roseanne*.

2. **Single-source feel** — nearly every load-bearing quote comes from the one Maron 2019 WTF episode, so it starts to read like a podcast recap walked top to bottom. Worth leaning a bit more on the Guardian/Bridges/Barr material or varying how the Maron quotes are framed.

Smaller notes cover the unpaid-off fatherhood mirror, the never-Oscar-nominated angle for the "underestimated" beat, a repeated "nothing to the party" phrase, and a recurring negation-then-assertion rhythm. Flagged the loud-onscreen/erased-offscreen spine and the "Gestapo" line as the things to preserve.

