## What I changed

I treated the Fresh Eyes notes as a strong but not-binding list, verified every new fact by web search, then made five edits:

**Added substance (the high-value gaps):**
- **SNL** — new paragraph in the cast section. Goodman hosted *Saturday Night Live* 13 times (1989–2013), third-most ever behind Steve Martin and Alec Baldwin, with the "Platinum Lounge" inside joke. This was the one real reader-expectation gap, and it's the cleanest proof of the thesis: a 9 returning year after year to a *family that was never even his show*, just to be useful in the room.
